Ms. H. Thi Houng, #09010010, is 32 yrs old and lives with her husband and 2 young children. Her family has many business activities for their income: raising chickens for eggs, ducks for meat, sows for breeding and meat, selling construction materials. In addition to raising animals, every day her husband works as a building contractor. Therefore, her family's income is quite stable ranging from 15.00 USD to 18.00 USD per day. She already went through one cycle of borrowing from the fund and repaying the loan, and she really likes this form of loan. It agrees with the goals and income of her family. This time she would like to borrow 260.00 USD to buy feed for the pigs, chickens and ducks. The other members in her group are:
Mr. Le Dac Chinh, #09010007, loan amount 260.00 USD to raise pigs;
Mr. Le Dac Tuyen, # 09010016, loan amount 195.00 USD to buy chicken feed;
Ms. Le Thi Hang, # 09010012, loan amount 260.00 USD to raise pigs;
MS. Nguyen Thi Toan, # 09010018, loan amount 195.00 USD to buy scrap iron (repay in 25 weeks);
Ms. Nguyn Thi Hien, # 09010017, loan amount 130.00 USD to supplement buying feed for pigs (repay in 25 weeks)



<br /><p><strong>Translated from Vietnamese by Thu Ostrander, Kiva Volunteer</strong></p>
